[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-19T21:37:21+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot from Civilization VI featuring Julius Ceaser the world leader for the Roman faction\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/mtKzwct-Kna0CoxGD59l92yU4ko=/101x0:644x362/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73597786/Civ6_Caesar_embed.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Firaxis / 2K Games</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"2pYNNV\">Netflix\u2019s newest games are actually a bit old. During its Geeked Week 2024 presentation, the streaming service revealed it\u2019s adding <em>Civilization VI</em> and <em>Street Fighter IV: Champion Edition</em> as well as a host of other titles to its ever-increasing and legitimately impressive gaming lineup.</p>\n<p id=\"RRNeqA\">For <em>Civ 6,</em> players will have access to all the game\u2019s expansion packs that were a part of the Platinum Edition version of the game. Meanwhile, Netflix will host the Champion Edition of <em>Street Fighter IV</em> featuring all 32 fighters released over the game\u2019s lifetime. Al", "id": 1179060, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/19/24249136/netflix-civilization-6-street-fighter-4-game-releases", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Netflix adds Civilization VI and Street Fighter IV to its games lineup", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-19T21:04:21+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A woman looking at herself in the mirror while smearing black face paint down her cheek.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/yPK4FzTc3591eco4ff7HNfMngEY=/708x0:3948x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73597741/Arcane_u_S2_00_00_53_06.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Netflix</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"VAZ5Q0\">The <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24172175/arcane-league-of-legends-season-2-trailer-netflix\">second and final season of Netflix\u2019s <em>Arcane</em></a><em> </em>finally has a concrete release date, but it looks like the episodes won\u2019t all be dropping at once.</p>\n<p id=\"FL7Rs5\">This evening, during the final night of this year\u2019s Geeked Week showcase, <a href=\"https://www.netflix.com/tudum/articles/arcane-season-2-release-date-photos\">Netflix and Riot announced</a> that <em>Arcane\u2019s </em>final season will be a three-part event. Act One is set to premiere on November 9th, Act Two debuts on November 16th, and Act Three", "id": 1178913, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/19/24236186/netflix-arcane-season-2-premiere-date-trailer", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Arcane\u2019s final season starts streaming on November 9th", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-19T20:44:41+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A still image from the Netflix series Devil May Cry.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ei4xokG84AtSUIdXMPxWyuK9mjc=/144x0:1157x675/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73597729/AAAAQZy3OkRC9CJH6qWTfr8GCL3dc5fR7tezqDNoPPjFBiwhRrSf3HCa_fQrGIwH1cOVcmu3p_AMivmB0ARKLCjtgISsa4WDVH0rPrcvz_5tn8fKoek8VuYmOT3EsBJTHaYjRM68QHSzwvm5Uyp_M18iar2RSXQ.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Netflix</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"WEuaWl\">It doesn\u2019t look like Dante has lost a step for his upcoming animated series. Netflix just released a new trailer for <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23889805/devil-may-cry-anime-netflix-trailer\">its <em>Devil May Cry</em> adaptation</a>, and it includes the kind of absurd, over-the-top demon-hunting action that has made <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/3/6/18252281/devil-may-cry-5-review-ps4-xbox-pc\">Capcom\u2019s games so beloved</a>. That means big swords, motorcycle chases, dual-wielding pistols, and... guns ", "id": 1178914, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/19/24249440/devil-may-cry-show-netflix-date-trailer", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Netflix\u2019s Devil May Cry series starts streaming in April", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-19T20:16:01+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A still image from the animated series Splinter Cell: Deathwatch.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/EZpWMEsbrsG7iBY5dGb0XT_SDlk=/453x0:1818x910/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73597716/Screen_Shot_2024_09_19_at_8.14.32_PM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Netflix</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"W59qCZ\">It\u2019s been quite some time since we heard anything about <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2020/7/30/21348468/netflix-splinter-cell-animated-series-adaptation-witcher-castlevania-john-wick\">Netflix\u2019s animated adaptation of <em>Splinter Cell</em></a> \u2014 but the streamer has finally provided some details on the show. The reveal comes in the form of a very brief teaser trailer, which shows a little bit of the show, but mostly showcases Liev Schreiber\u2019s gravelly take on lead character Sam Fisher. We also have a proper name now: it\u2019s called <em>Splinter Cell: Deathwatch</em>.</p>\n<p id=\"MXzwYG\">The show is being written by Derek ", "id": 1178485, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/19/24249426/splinter-cell-deathwatch-netflix-animated-series-teaser-trailer", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Netflix teases its animated Splinter Cell series", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-19T20:14:47+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of actress Miya Cech.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/HXKw26x3oHzoV02EeFLhl8nmiSc=/94x0:1107x675/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73597714/slack_imgs.5.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Netflix</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"zvtLmP\">It\u2019s not clear how much of <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24071094/netflix-avatar-last-airbender-review\"><em>Avatar: The Last Airbender</em></a>\u2019s story Netflix will fit into <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/6/24092243/netflix-avatar-the-last-airbender-season-2-renewal\">the next season of its live-action adaptation</a>, but we now know who will be portraying the series\u2019 take on Toph.</p>\n<p id=\"HFCva9\">During Netflix\u2019s ongoing Geeked Week event, the streamer announced that Miya Cech (<em>Beef</em>, <em>American Girl: Corinne Tan</em>) <a href=\"https://www.netflix.com/tudum/articles/avatar-the-last-airbender-live-action-toph-miya-cech\">has been cast as Toph Beifong</a>, the ", "id": 1178486, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/19/24249436/netflix-the-last-airbender-toph-season-2", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Netflix\u2019s Avatar: The Last Airbender has found its Toph", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-19T18:35:35+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of a person holding a US passport and an envelope.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/dRR8XtXh7WyEujzFpZbm9E66UyQ=/0x85:2040x1445/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73597543/passport_2040.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>The Verge<em>\u2019s</em> <em>Sean Hollister picking up his new passport at the post office.</em> | Photo by Sean Hollister / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ii9u3A\">If you read my colleague Sean Hollister\u2019s positive experience <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/3/24190366/us-passport-online-renewal-beta-fast\">renewing his US passport online</a> through a beta website from the State Department \u2014 without needing to ship his old passport \u2014 I have good news for you: that experience is now available for everyone. You can access it <a href=\"https://travel.state.gov/content/travel/en/passports/have-passport/renew-online.html\">right here</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"Al3Jmj\">\u201cInstead of printing a paper application ", "id": 1178487, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/19/24249413/us-online-passport-renewal-website", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "US online passport renewal is now fully open for business", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-19T17:56:22+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Concord illustration\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-frqQdHXN_CLRihG5KsaPE6wCjQ=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73597416/ad3527b123d0c8dfcca5d4968a6dcf126e37a68dd290ef85.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Sony</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"tji3n8\"><em>Concord</em> game director Ryan Ellis has stepped down following the decision to take the game offline, <a href=\"https://kotaku.com/concord-firewalk-studios-relaunch-ps5-sony-playstation-1851652811\">according to <em>Kotaku</em></a>. Developers at <em>Concord</em> developer Firewalk Studios are also uncertain of the future of the studio.</p>\n<p id=\"BPUAoa\">Ellis, whose resume also includes more than seven years at Bungie, informed staff of the change role last week, <em>Kotaku</em> reports. (His LinkedIn still lists his title as \u201cGame Director.\u201d) Ellis also authored the PlayStation Blog post <a href=\"https://blog.playstation.com/2024/09/03/an-important-u", "id": 1178082, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/19/24249358/sony-playstation-concord-director-steps-down", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Concord\u2019s director reportedly steps down", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-19T16:03:11+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration featuring eyes and locks\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/VzwH7dIpQ6Im6JSRXzIZto6Jn-c=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73596989/acastro_190204_1777_privacy_0002.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"FOQEkb\">The Federal Trade Commission published a <a href=\"https://www.ftc.gov/news-events/news/press-releases/2024/09/ftc-staff-report-finds-large-social-media-video-streaming-companies-have-engaged-vast-surveillance\">new report</a> about the data collection policies of social media platforms and video streaming services, and the results are damning, if not unexpected. The report, which was released on September 19th, found that these platforms not only surveil consumers but often retain vast troves of data indefinitely about users and non-users alike \u2014 and suggests they can\u2019t be trusted to regulate themselves.</p>\n<p id=\"Y9L9pG\">Given", "id": 1177705, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/19/24249073/ftc-data-retention-privacy-report-facebook-meta-youtube-reddit", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The FTC says social media companies can\u2019t be trusted to regulate themselves", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-19T15:59:53+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A graphic of Logitech\u2019s G502 X Plus AL Edition limited-edition mouse.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/1ykjCnBjCEIvz4BcFbyCpIVubLg=/115x0:966x567/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73596966/g502_10yr_anniversary_kv_still_one_1.1.1_gleam_copy.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Logitech</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"wFU2Q5\">Logitech is celebrating the 10th anniversary of its G502 gaming mouse with <a href=\"https://imp.i140643.net/c/482924/546180/9160?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.logitech.com%2Fblog%2F2024%2F09%2F17%2Fintroducing-the-g502-aluminum-celebrating-a-decade-of-innovation-and-excellence%2F&amp;sharedid=theverge.com\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">a limited-edition aluminum version</a>. The G502 X Plus AL Edition has the same functionality as the standard wireless G502 X mouse, plus an aluminum chassis with laser-etched markings, including a serial number from 1 to 502. </p>\n<p id=\"WxLqqD\">Sorry to put my ", "id": 1177706, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/19/24249195/logitech-g502-limited-edition-aluminum-10th-anniversary-gaming-mouse", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Logitech is making 502 metal mice", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-19T15:37:50+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of Apple devices running Apple Intelligence.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/x6ia9bMDRCzIVe1aBeSN4oq6ybk=/154x0:1807x1102/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73596907/Apple_WWDC24_Apple_Intelligence_hero_240610.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Apple</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"91H4v0\">Apple has just released public betas of iOS 18.1, iPadOS 18.1, and macOS Sequoia 15.1, and they include upcoming Apple Intelligence features like text rewriting tools, the glowy new Siri design, a \u201cClean Up\u201d tool to remove objects from your photos, and more.</p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><aside id=\"Gg11Se\"><div data-anthem-component=\"readmore\" data-anthem-component-data='{\"stories\":[{\"title\":\"A first look at Apple Intelligence and its (slightly) smarter Siri\",\"url\":\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/31/24209910/apple-intelligence-ios-18-preview-siri\"},{\"title\":\"Apple Intelligence will come to more languages over the ne", "id": 1177346, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/19/24249206/apple-intelligence-ios-18-1-public-beta", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple Intelligence is now available in public betas", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-19T14:59:38+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Three screenshots of the Hipstamatic Party! app running on an iPhone.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/VpFkAjTa23ibNVhu6bJOocl9Dy8=/0x0:1500x1000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73596790/hipstamatic1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Hipstamatic Party! Disposable Camera app saves event organizers from having to chase down guests to get their photos.</em> | Screenshot: Apple App Store</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"4PaAUr\">Hipstamatic\u2019s new <a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/party-disposable-camera/id6504739136\">Party! Disposable Camera app</a> is designed to digitally replicate the experience of guests snapping candid photos at a wedding or other event using a disposable film camera. There are no film development fees afterward, but it\u2019s only free if your guest list is no larger than five people.</p>\n<p id=\"RiIVwS\">At its core, the app is yet another attempt to streamline the process of collecting all the smartpho", "id": 1177347, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/19/24248903/hipstamatic-disposable-camera-app-ios-iphone", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27