runs into you", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-19T14:44:32+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Woman looking at the app grid on the Apple Watch SE (2022).\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/OLKTCa3INedwxe5jpmI0MVU5GKc=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73596749/226292_Apple_Watch_SE_PHO_akrales_0222.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>watchOS 11 makes the Apple Watch an even better remote for the Apple TV.</em> | Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Bl0fwk\">Previous versions of watchOS allowed the Apple Watch to be used as a remote control for the Apple TV with limited functionality. With <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/16/24246171/apple-watchos-11-watch-sleep-apnea-smartwatch-launch\">watchOS 11</a>, the smartwatch can potentially completely replace the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22446699/apple-tv-4k-hd-siri-remote-review-features-price\">Siri Remote</a> that now ships with Apple\u2019s streaming box, with new capabilities <a href=\"https://9to5mac.com/2024/09/", "id": 1177015, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/19/24249074/apple-watch-watchos-11-tv-remote", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Apple Watch is now a better TV remote", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-19T14:13:10+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Cruise in San Francisco\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/gFNqK8ETwuBTKDkYilCaDkxZujc=/1x0:4000x2666/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73596652/1590511768.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo: Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"NN1QeB\">Almost a year since the horrifying crash in which one of its driverless vehicles ran over and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/24/23930629/california-dmv-suspends-cruise-robotaxi-permit-safety\">dragged a woman 20 feet</a>, Cruise is planning its return to the Bay Area. The company said <a href=\"https://x.com/Cruise/status/1836812363963486286\">in a post on X</a> that it is deploying \u201cseveral\u201d manually driven mapping vehicles in Sunnyvale and Mountain View, with the goal of progressing to \u201csupervised testing\u201d with five autonomous vehicles later this fall. </p>\n<p id=\"lEQ7z1\">\u201cResuming testing in the Bay Area is an important step forward as we continue to work closely with Califo", "id": 1177016, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/19/24249150/cruise-robotaxi-sf-return-manual-drive-autonomous", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Cruise plots its robotaxi return to the Bay Area", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-19T12:59:44+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"LG\u2019s C4 OLED TV in a living room turned on with surfers on the display.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/DRKx7yei3OFB8dWUmr-w0zEO7hk=/0x44:721x525/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73596486/lgc4oled.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>You can save well over $1,000 on LG\u2019s vibrant 65-inch C4 OLED TV.</em> | Image: LG</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"5QWsBJ\"><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/17/24244180/amazon-october-prime-day-big-deal-days-fall-dates